sql:
SELECT ticker, one_year_price_performance
FROM etfs
ORDER BY one_year_price_performance DESC;

SELECT ticker, fund_name, net_expense_ratio
FROM etfs
WHERE etf_id = 0;

SELECT fund_name, ticker, esg_score
FROM etfs
WHERE esg_score = (SELECT MAX(esg_score) FROM etfs);

external_knowledge:
- A net expense ratio is the total percentage of a fund's assets that are used to cover operational expenses, after any fee waivers or reimbursements; 
- A one-year price performance refers to the change in the price of the fund over a one-year period;
- Assets under management (AUM) refers to the total market value of all assets that an ETF manages on behalf of its investors.

sql:
SELECT ticker, fund_name 
FROM etfs 
WHERE esg_score > (SELECT esg_score FROM etfs WHERE etf_id = 1);

SELECT SUM(market_value) AS total_market_value
FROM holdings
WHERE etf_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Leaders of the pack" refers to the top-ranked ETFs; 
- "Outperformed the market" means having a one-year price performance greater than 5%; 
- "Versatility score" is a metric calculated by subtracting the number of unique holdings from the average price performance, indicating how well an ETF balances performance and diversification.
